										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Over <a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/instagram-stats/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">200 million</a> businesses are on Instagram marketing their brand, connecting with customers, and more. Are you one of them? With this complete Instagram marketing guide, you can be!</p>
<p>While Instagram marketing sounds a lot easier said than done, it can be well worth it to take the time to get up and running on this flourishing social platform. Many Instagram users are constantly on the lookout for new brands to follow and buy from, making it the perfect outlet for your promotional content.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs why we‚Äôre covering everything you need to know to get started with Instagram marketing, and how you can optimize your strategy using free tools, templates, and more.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-what">What is Instagram marketing?</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-benefits">Why market on Instagram?</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-types">Types of Instagram posts</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-start">How to get started with Instagram marketing</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-tips">Our top Instagram marketing tips</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-examples">Instagram marketing examples</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-tools">Free Instagram marketing tools</a></li>
<li><a href="#instagram-marketing-templates">Free Instagram marketing post templates</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="instagram-marketing-what"></div>
<h2>What is Instagram marketing?</h2>
<p>Instagram marketing is the practice of using the social media platform, Instagram, to grow your business through tactics like organic (a.k.a. free) posts, Reels, Stories, follower interactions, account partnerships and more.</p>
<p>Instagram has different feeds available that allow users to browse and discover image and video content, which is how your customers can connect with your business on the app.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-example-home-feed.webp" alt="instagram marketing - home feed" width="297" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94273 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-example-home-feed.webp 297w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-example-home-feed-149x300.webp 149w" sizes="(max-width: 297px) 100vw, 297px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>An example Instagram feed.</em></p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f9e9.png" alt="üß©" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Instagram marketing is just one piece of your business&#8217;s brand awareness puzzle.</strong> Download our<a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLTheDefinitiveGuideBrandAwareness.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_BrandAwareness_Guide_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> definitive guide to brand awareness</a> to get more top strategies and examples for business growth.</p>
<h3>What‚Äôs the difference between Instagram marketing and Instagram advertising?</h3>
<p>Instagram marketing includes all your free, organic efforts on Instagram.</p>
<p>Instagram advertising is done through the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-advertise-on-facebook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Ads platform</a> and requires campaign budgets to pay for your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/08/instagram-ads-cost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ad placements across the Instagram network</a>. That said, though, <strong>you can always ‚Äúboost‚Äù a single organic Instagram post with a smaller, one-time budget</strong>‚Äîwhich can be done directly from the Instagram platform.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-ad.webp" alt="instagram marketing - ad example" width="284" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94278 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-ad.webp 284w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-ad-142x300.webp 142w" sizes="(max-width: 284px) 100vw, 284px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Unlike organic Instagram posts, Instagram Ads and boosted posts will have a ‚Äúsponsored‚Äù line as well as a CTA button attached to them, like </em><a href="https://www.creatopy.com/blog/instagram-ads-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>the above example</em></a><em>. </em></p>
<p>While Instagram marketing might still require some budget to really take off, it‚Äôs generally cheaper than Instagram advertising‚Äîmaking it a no-brainer for every business type out there.</p>
<p>However,<strong> Instagram advertising allows you to tap into more audiences </strong>that might not necessarily be following your business but are more likely to convert into customers. That‚Äôs why <strong>it‚Äôs best to use a combination of both Instagram marketing and advertising</strong> to maximize your brand‚Äôs success on the platform.</p>
<p>You can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/instagram-advertising" target="_blank" rel="noopener">learn more about Instagram advertising</a> here, but for this post, we‚Äôll be focusing on Instagram marketing. After all, your Instagram ads will be more impactful if you have your Instagram marketing solidified first.</p>
<p><strong><span data-contrast="auto" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" class="TextRun SCXW170783564 BCX0"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW170783564 BCX0"><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> </span></span>Already running ads on Meta?</strong> See how they&#8217;re doing using our free, instant <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/facebook-advertising?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_FBGrader_FBGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook Ads Grader</a>!</p>
<div id="instagram-marketing-benefits"></div>
<h2>Why market on Instagram?</h2>
<p>Marketing on Instagram is a low-cost option for growth that any business can take advantage of. Aside from that, though, there are tons of other benefits to Instagram marketing. Consider these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/04/20/instagram-statistics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram facts and statistics</a>.</p>
<h3>Instagram holds a captive audience</h3>
<p>Instagram has a captive audience ready to pay attention to your business‚Äôs marketing. In fact, users spend about <a href="https://backlinko.com/instagram-users" target="_blank" rel="noopener">34 minutes</a> daily and <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1294879/time-spent-instagram-app-selected-countries/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">12 hours</a> monthly on Instagram on average‚Äîwhich is part of the reason why Instagram marketing is such a popular strategy.</p>
<p><span>Instagram users like to interact with businesses </span></p>
<p>Did you know that <a href="https://business.instagram.com/getting-started/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">20%</a> of Instagram users visit a business profile every single day? <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/social-media-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">90%</a> of Instagram users follow at least one business on the platform. Not only that, but <a href="https://business.instagram.com/getting-started/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">33%</a> of the most popular Instagram stories are shared by business accounts.</p>
<p>Instagram isn‚Äôt just favored for brand discovery, either, as you can use the platform to address <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/customer-pain-points/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">customer pain points</a> and improve the overall customer experience your business provides. In fact, <a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/instagram-stats/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">72%</a> of Gen Z consumers are most likely to use Instagram for customer service over any other platform.</p>
<h3>Instagram users are ready to convert</h3>
<p>Instagram is the <a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/instagram-stats/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">most popular</a> platform for product discovery, with <a href="https://business.instagram.com/getting-started/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">60%</a> of people saying they discover new products on Instagram. <a href="https://sproutsocial.com/insights/index/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">29%</a> of Instagram users make purchases directly from the platform, and <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">36%</a> of people say they use Instagram as a search tool like they would Google (although you can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/instagram-posts-indexed-on-google">optimize your Instagram posts for Google Search</a>, too).</p>
<p>Needless to say, Instagram users are ready to convert. <a href="https://www.businessdasher.com/instagram-statistics-for-business/#:~:text=87%25%20of%20Instagram%20users%20say,23%25%20more%20engagement%20than%20Facebook." target="_blank" rel="noopener">87%</a> of Instagram users take action, like visiting a website or making a purchase, after seeing a business‚Äôs Instagram post.</p>
<h3>Your competitors are likely already marketing on Instagram</h3>
<p>Odds are, your competitors are already finding success on Instagram. After all, Instagram is the third <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/instagram-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">most popular</a> social platform and the fourth most visited site in the world. Over <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/259379/social-media-platforms-used-by-marketers-worldwide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">80%</a> of small businesses market their brand on Instagram, and <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1284484/social-media-platforms-highest-return-on-investment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">29%</a> of businesses say Instagram yields them the highest <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-roi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing ROI</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-statistics.webp" alt="instagram marketing stats" width="898" height="674" class="aligncenter wp-image-94260 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-statistics.webp 898w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-statistics-480x360.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 898px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="instagram-marketing-types"></div>
<h2>Types of Instagram posts</h2>
<p>There are a few types of Instagram posts your business can use to market to potential customers. Let‚Äôs review:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Standard Instagram image posts: </strong>The original Instagram post type, which requires an image in order to be published.</li>
<li><strong>Instagram Reels: </strong>A short-form video post type that can be up to 3 minutes long.</li>
<li><strong>Carousel posts:</strong> This post type can be a combination of up to 20 different images and videos in a row that viewers can swipe through.</li>
<li><strong>Stories: </strong>Stories are a temporary style of an image or video post that only stays up for 24 hours. They are accessible by clicking on an account‚Äôs profile picture. However, note that you can also <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/instagram-highlight-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">save a story as a ‚Äúhighlight‚Äù</a> that stays at the top of your page. Or, you can go live on your story, too, and save any live footage as a story later. Check out some <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/instagram-story-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram story ideas</a> here.</li>
</ul>
<p>All Instagram post types allow you to add a caption, hashtags, music, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-add-location-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">location</a>, stickers, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-tag-someone-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">user tags</a>, and more.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-post-types.webp" alt="instagram marketing - types of instagram posts" width="885" height="775" class="aligncenter wp-image-94258 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-post-types.webp 885w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-post-types-480x420.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 885px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Where can your Instagram posts show up?</h3>
<p>All your Instagram posts (no matter the format) will be shown in your followers‚Äô home feeds, which will look like the example we saw above.</p>
<p>Your business‚Äôs posts and Reels can also appear on the Instagram explore page, where people can view your content regardless of whether they follow you or not.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-explore-page.webp" alt="instagram marketing - explore page screenshot" width="277" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94274 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-explore-page.webp 277w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-explore-page-139x300.webp 139w" sizes="(max-width: 277px) 100vw, 277px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://about.instagram.com/features/reels" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>Your Reels can also be viewed by both followers and non-followers in the Reels tab. The Reels tab is where users can scroll through Reels similarly to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/tiktok-algorithm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TikTok</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-reels.webp" alt="instagram marketing - reels page screenshot" width="337" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94279 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-reels.webp 337w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-reels-169x300.webp 169w" sizes="(max-width: 337px) 100vw, 337px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.socialpilot.co/blog/instagram-reels-algorithm" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<h3>Instagram post sizes and specs</h3>
<p>With so many options and flexibility when it comes to Instagram post placements, the sizing and specs you should aim for when creating images and videos will vary. Here‚Äôs a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/social-media-image-sizes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">breakdown of Instagram sizing</a>:</p>
<ul>
<li>Instagram profile photo: 320 x 320 px</li>
<li>Instagram image posts: 1080 x 1440 px</li>
<li>Instagram landscape image posts: 1080 x 566 px</li>
<li>Instagram portrait image posts: 1080 x 1350 px</li>
<li>Instagram Stories and Reels: 1080 x 1920 px</li>
<li>Instagram Reel cover image size: 420 x 654 px</li>
</ul>
<p>As a bonus, if you want to plan out your profile tiles for a top-tier account aesthetic, try testing out how your images might look in the 161 x 161 px thumbnail size.</p>
<p>Note that there is also some flexibility with sizing on Instagram. For example, the Instagram profile picture minimum size is technically 110 x 110 px. Or, when creating a carousel post of image and video slides in different sizes, there‚Äôs a square button that allows you to opt to have the slides stay in their original sizes rather than being automatically cropped to the same size. Also, <span data-teams="true">Instagram image posts used to be square but they have since <a href="https://help.instagram.com/1631821640426723" target="_blank" rel="noopener">updated the display size</a>, although you can still upload square images as long as they&#8217;re 1080 height. </span></p>
<p>Instagram also tends to compress images in posts that are uploaded in a larger file size than allowed, so try saving your Instagram content files in the most compact format possible without sacrificing quality. Read on for some tools to help with this.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-size-chart.webp" alt="instagram marketing - sizing" width="900" height="488" class="aligncenter wp-image-94962 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-size-chart.webp 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-size-chart-480x260.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="instagram-marketing-start"></div>
<h2>How to get started with Instagram marketing</h2>
<p>Ready to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-drive-traffic-from-instagram" target="_blank" rel="noopener">jumpstart your business‚Äôs Instagram</a> marketing journey? Follow these six steps.</p>
<h3>1. Create your Instagram business account</h3>
<p>There are two ways you can <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-create-a-new-instagram-account/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">create a new Instagram account</a>. The first option is navigating to <a href="https://www.instagram.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.instagram.com</a> directly and following the prompts to create an account. Alternatively, you could download the Instagram app and sign up that way.</p>
<p>For either of these two options, you could also sync your Facebook account to have your new Instagram account loaded up with your Facebook profile details. If you want to go this route, you‚Äôll need an <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-advertise-on-facebook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">account set up on Meta</a> via <a href="https://business.facebook.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://business.facebook.com/</a>.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs no right or wrong account creation option, and they‚Äôre all equally popular, so it depends on what might be best for your Instagram marketing needs. For example, if your business is already well established on Facebook, it may be easiest to just sync your Facebook page. Or, maybe you‚Äôre launching a full Meta marketing strategy for a new brand, in which case you might want to get set up via the Meta Business Manager first.</p>
<p>Once you have your account, <strong>be sure it&#8217;s set as a business Instagram account </strong>by clicking the ‚Äúedit profile‚Äù button at the top of your account‚Äôs page. Tap the <strong>switch to professional account</strong> prompt at the bottom of the edit profile page. From there, you can follow the prompts to select a category for your business, add contact details, and so on.</p>
<p>Here are some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/10/best-business-instagram-accounts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">example Instagram business accounts</a> to get some ideas of how to arrange your own account.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-professional-account.webp" alt="instagram marketing - professional account option" width="276" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94268 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-professional-account.webp 276w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-professional-account-138x300.webp 138w" sizes="(max-width: 276px) 100vw, 276px" /></p>
<h3>2. Decide what to track and set your goals</h3>
<p>Your Instagram marketing goals will help you determine what types of Instagram content you want to focus on, how much of your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-budget/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing budget</a> will be put towards your strategy, and more. The SMART (specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and timely) goal structure can <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/instagram-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">guide your Instagram</a> goal planning during this step.</p>
<p>You might also want to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/facebook-ads-benchmarks-2025" target="_blank" rel="noopener">check out industry benchmarks</a> to see the average performance for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/11/01/instagram-analytics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">key Instagram metrics</a> in your industry.</p>
<p><strong>Here are some Instagram marketing metrics to consider including in your goals:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Likes: </strong>Total number of users who clicked the ‚Äúheart‚Äù button on your post.</li>
<li><strong>Comments:</strong> Total number of users who commented on your post.</li>
<li><strong>Shares: </strong>Total number of times a user sent your post to other users via <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-dm-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram direct messages</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Saves:</strong> Total number of users who saved your content to their archives.</li>
<li><strong>Views:</strong> The number of times your post or reel was displayed on a user‚Äôs screen.</li>
<li><strong>Profile visits: </strong>Total number of times users visited your business‚Äôs Instagram profile.</li>
<li><strong>Reach:</strong> Total number of unique accounts that saw your Instagram content at least once.</li>
<li><strong>Follower count: </strong>The number of accounts that follow your business‚Äôs page. Ideally, you want more or roughly the same number of accounts to be following you as you follow, known as your <strong>follower ratio</strong>. This makes your brand appear more desirable.</li>
</ul>
<p>Of course, there are a ton of other actions and engagements you can track to measure your Instagram marketing results‚Äîdon‚Äôt forget about end-goal conversions like website visits, sales, or leads. The point is to add a bit of structure to your strategy here.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-metrics.webp" alt="instagram marketing metrics chart" width="868" height="659" class="aligncenter wp-image-94259 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-metrics.webp 868w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-metrics-480x364.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 868px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>3. Identify your target audience</h3>
<p>Now that you know your big picture goals for your Instagram marketing strategy, you can start thinking about <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/instagram-ad-targeting" target="_blank" rel="noopener">who you want to tailor your content to</a>. Check out some <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/target-market-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">target market examples</a>, and don‚Äôt be afraid to creep on your competitors‚Äô or ideal customers‚Äô follower and following lists. That way, you can get an idea of what types of users might see your Instagram content and how to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/10/27/brand-messaging" target="_blank" rel="noopener">adjust your messaging</a> accordingly.</p>
<h3>4. Plan your posts</h3>
<p>Time to start brainstorming what to post when. A social media <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-calendar/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing calendar</a> can come in handy during this step. You may need to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/always-on-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">factor in seasonality</a>, upcoming product launches, events, promotions, and sales to get your post ideation and planning off the ground.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/2025-marketing-calendar-december-1024x638.webp" alt="december 2025 marketing calendar" width="1024" height="638" class="aligncenter wp-image-87771 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/2025-marketing-calendar-december-980x611.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/2025-marketing-calendar-december-480x299.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong><span data-contrast="auto" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" class="TextRun SCXW58581821 BCX0"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXW58581821 BCX0"><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4c6.png" alt="üìÜ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></span></span><span class="EOP SCXW58581821 BCX0" data-ccp-props="{}"> ¬†</span>Download this<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/marketing-calendar?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025MarketingCalendar_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> free marketing calendar template</a> here!</strong></p>
<h3>5. Create and publish your posts</h3>
<p>This is arguably the most fun step in the Instagram marketing process: executing on your posts! You can <strong>click the plus sign </strong>at the bottom center of your Instagram screen to start posting.</p>
<p>Instagram allows you to create posts ahead of time and save them as drafts, or you can use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/01/17/best-free-social-media-management-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">third-party tools</a> and marketing partners to do the heavy lifting for you when it comes to post creation, scheduling and optimization.</p>
<h3>6. Track your performance</h3>
<p>As you continue to post and engage on Instagram to promote your business, you‚Äôll need to keep a close eye on how everything is going. You‚Äôll probably want to use third-party tools and marketing partners for complete Instagram reports, but the first place you should go during this step is directly into the <strong>dashboard</strong> of creator tools offered within the platform.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-creator-tools.webp" alt="instagram marketing -creator tools screenshot" width="304" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94255 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-creator-tools.webp 304w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-creator-tools-152x300.webp 152w" sizes="(max-width: 304px) 100vw, 304px" /></p>
<p>From there, you can click into a few different<strong> insights </strong>pages.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-insights.webp" alt="instagram marketing - insights page" width="275" height="503" class="aligncenter wp-image-94256 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-insights.webp 275w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-insights-164x300.webp 164w" sizes="(max-width: 275px) 100vw, 275px" /></p>
<div id="instagram-marketing-tips"></div>
<h2>Our top Instagram marketing tips</h2>
<p>Once you get up and running on Instagram, keep these tips in mind.</p>
<h3>Be active and engage with content</h3>
<p>A critical step in the <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/instagram-marketing-tips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram marketing process</a> is interacting with your followers and the people you want to follow you.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre already posting follow-worthy content, then start liking, commenting, and following others. For instance, search popular hashtags and like away! Write complimentary comments on people‚Äôs posts and repost from others to gain attention.</p>
<p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> You can opt to get notifications when accounts you‚Äôre targeting share a new post, so you can interact with it sooner rather than later.</p>
<h3>Test out different types of content</h3>
<p>You might find that certain post types resonate best with different audiences. Don‚Äôt be afraid to flex your content and test as needed. For example, Reels tend to <a href="https://www.socialinsider.io/blog/instagram-benchmarks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">double</a> your reach as opposed to standard posts. So, if you‚Äôre prioritizing reach, you could post more Reels instead of image posts.</p>
<h3>Set up an Instagram Shop</h3>
<p>For businesses promoting products, an Instagram Shop is a quick and easy way to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/11/15/selling-on-instagram" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sell on Instagram</a>. Users can click on your Instagram Shop to make purchases without having to leave the platform. You can learn more about Instagram Shops and how to set them up <a href="https://help.instagram.com/194353285783006/?helpref=breadcrumb" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-shops.webp" alt="instagram marketing - instagram shops" width="629" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-94277 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-shops.webp 629w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/instagram-marketing-shops-480x458.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 629px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://business.instagram.com/blog/introducing-shops-on-instagram" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<h3>Sync your Instagram strategy with other marketing channels</h3>
<p>Consider how your Instagram marketing could impact your other <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-channels/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">promotional channels</a>, and vice versa. For example, you‚Äôll likely want to be promoting your business‚Äôs Instagram account across other placements like your website, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-promote-your-youtube-channel" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube channel</a>, and more. Additionally, always be thinking about how you can recycle other marketing materials into Instagram posts.</p>
<p>You should be striving to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/06/22/cross-channel-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">provide a seamless cross-channel experience</a> for your potential customers, so be sure that whatever you‚Äôre posting on Instagram aligns with what you‚Äôre promoting elsewhere.</p>
<h3>Use hashtags carefully</h3>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-use-hashtags-with-hashtag-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hashtags</a> can be a game-changer when you‚Äôre trying to get found on Instagram. However, there are some outdated hashtag practices you‚Äôll want to avoid. It‚Äôs best to prioritize only the most popular or relevant hashtags in your post captions, as stuffing your captions with tons of custom hashtags is a thing of the past.</p>
<p>Not only that, but you might consider moving your hashtags down in your post caption so they‚Äôre not as apparent. Today, users are much more aware of how hashtags help businesses gain more traction on social media. Using them too prominently in your post captions could come off a bit ‚Äúdesperate‚Äù for views and likes.</p>
<h3>Try using AI</h3>
<p>There are a ton of different <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-prompts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ways you can use AI to optimize your Instagram</a> creative, brainstorm captions, and more. Whether you‚Äôre using the Meta AI features within the Instagram platform or trying out third-party AI tools, be sure to give any AI-generated content an extra edit manually to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/brand-consistency/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">maintain brand consistency</a> and credibility.</p>
